    with Albury.

Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Stadhampton. 
    See also Table 2, note (h).
Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Tetsworth.

Abolished 1.4.1932 and divided between the parishes of Great Milton 
    and Wheatley. See also Table 2, note (h).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Cuxham with 
    Easington. See also Table 2, note (h).
Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Chinnor.

On 25.3.1886 the part in Oxfordshire became 
    part of the parish of Waterstock, so that thereafter Ickford was entirely in Buckinghamshire. 
    See also Table 2, note (g).

On 30.9.1895 the part in Buckinghamshire was transferred to Oxfordshire, so that thereafter Kingsey was 
    entirely in Oxfordshire. 
    See also Table 2, notes (d) and (h).

Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Tiddington 
    with Albury.

Created 1.4.1932 from the separate parishes of Tiddington and 
    Albury. See also Table 2, note (h).
Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Chalgrove.

That part which until 1.4.1932 formed part of the parish of 
    Easington. See also Table 2, note (h).

That part which until 1.4.1932 formed part of the parish of 
    Ascott. See also Table 2, note (h).

That part which until 1.4.1932 formed part of the parish of 
    Chilworth. See also Table 2, note (h).
